[[File:Immersea geo map.png|thumb|350x350px|''A map of the [[Wyvernwater]] and the town of Immersea.'']]
Immersea stood on the [[Calantar's Way]] and was most commonly used as a stop-over for travelers who ventured to and from [[Arabel]] and [[Hilp]]. Immer Stream began on the lush [[Spring Hill]] just west of the Redstoen Caste and cascade off the hill forming beautiful [[Selûne's Stairs]].{{Cite dragon/365/Backdrop: Cormyr|17-18}}

Immersea was known for its storms. The reputation birthed a Cormyrean saying, "scowling like an Immersea storm." Mists are very common, and much of the land was covered in flowering vines.

Notable Locations.Stores & Merchants:
*[[Alzael's Cleaver]], a busy and prosperous butchers shop ran by "Thousandslayer" [[Alzael]] in the in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].
*[[Carra Chulsanth's Carriageworks]], a simple smithy in the 14{{th}} century DR, taken over by [[Carra Chulsanth]] of [[Marsember]] in the 15{{th}} century DR.{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220523203950/https://twitter.com/TheEdVerse/status/1528837649288634371| title = TheEdVerse on Twitter| accessdate = 5-23-2022| date = 5-23-2022}}
*[[Chalasse's Fine Clothing]], ran by [[Chalasse]], a seller of finery from [[Suzail]] in the late 14{{th}} century [[DR]].
*[[Embrar’s Barn]], home and shop of [[Ambaerand Tansreth]], a capable 15{{th}} century blacksmith.{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20220523203520/https://twitter.com/TheEdVerse/status/1528835067979628546| title = TheEdVerse on Twitter| accessdate = 5-23-2022| date = 5-23-2022}}
*[[Nelzol's Notions]], a huge barn repurposed to he a hardware and vehicle store.
